PN,31706
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1774515910
OL,3,CAn economic snapshot of Britain on the
OL,4,Ceve of war
OL,6,FGas and electricity bills have not
OL,7,Freturned to pre-2022 levels. The Ofgem
OL,8,Fprice cap offers support until the end
OL,9,Fof July, but the unit price of energy
OL,10,Fis expected to rise by at least 30%
OL,11,Ffor households thereafter.
OL,13,FEnergy-intensive businesses - in
OL,14,Fsteel, chemicals and car-making -
OL,15,Fargue they were already on the back
OL,16,Ffoot, struggling to compete with
OL,17,Frivals abroad who pay less for
OL,18,Felectricity.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31707
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1774515910
OL,3,CAn economic snapshot of Britain on the
OL,4,Ceve of war
OL,6,FEveryone wants support, and an
OL,7,Funpopular government - whose finances
OL,8,Fare also under pressure from rising
OL,9,Foil prices and higher borrowing costs
OL,10,F- is working out how best to spread
OL,11,Fthe pain.
OL,13,FWe have moved seamlessly from one
OL,14,Feconomic shock to another - the first
OL,15,Fmade in Russia, the second made in
OL,16,FAmerica.
OL,18,FA month ago, on the eve of war, now
OL,19,Ffeels like a much happier time.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/8
